  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Peel and cut the <strong>shallots</strong> into wedges</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>shallot wedges</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly softened and beginning to caramelise</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1659369969895-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1659369969895-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1659369969895-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1659369969895-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1659369969895-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the shallots are cooking, cut the <strong>sausages</strong> into thirds</p><p>Once slightly softened, add the<strong> sausages pieces</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1659369972357-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1659369972357-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1659369972357-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1659369972357-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1659369972357-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> into quarters</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> in 250ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [425ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>mustardy stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1659369975103-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1659369975103-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1659369975103-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1659369975103-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1659369975103-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> </strong>sausages have browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour </strong>and cook for 1 min further or until the flour has dissolved</p><p>Reduce the heat to medium and add the<strong> chopped potatoes</strong> and<strong> mustardy stock </strong>with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and cook, covered, for 20-22 min or until the potatoes are fork tender and sausages are cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
